# Accepted Trivy findings, with reasons.

# Instances need outbound access (apt, Tigris over HTTPS, AWS APIs). Restricting
# egress by CIDR isn't practical for general internet egress.
AWS-0104

# The Tigris secret uses the AWS-managed Secrets Manager key. A customer-managed
# key is overkill for this demo.
AWS-0098

# The toolchain image is a local/CI dev image, run as root by design.
DS-0002
# ...and it's not a long-running service, so no HEALTHCHECK.
DS-0026
